comment.body:
@taysea, I've given it a shot, but to no ease of success.

The best I could arrive at was something like the following:

```js
// Test itself is marked async
const user = userEvent.setup();
...
const select = getByPlaceholderText('test select');
await user.click(select);
await waitFor(() => expect(getAllByRole('searchbox')[0]).toHaveFocus());
// Select does not respond to navigation if event is directed at the search input
await user.type(document.getElementById('test-select__select-drop'), '[ArrowDown]');
// Search input does unfocus
await waitFor(() => expect(getAllByRole('searchbox')[0]).not.toHaveFocus());
// But the focus is instead directed at a container element and not the first option
await waitFor(() => expect(getAllByRole('option')[0]).toHaveFocus());
```
I should also add that I tried `user.keyboard`, which fell short of even being able to shift focus (i.e. respond to the arrow down) once the drop appears.

This is presumably because the latter acts on the element in focus. However, as I've noted, dispatching the arrow down key while the search input is in focus causes the Select to not respond (i.e. something must be swallowing up that event?).

If I contrast this with my existing test, that single `fireEvent.keyDown` invocation, plus a delay, was able to correctly (or at least for the purpose of the test) simulate a keyboard navigation step and to also focus the first option as expected.

Any suggestions on your part? I'm not sure what to do at this stage if there's insistence on `userEvent` being used instead.

Otherwise I'll update the bundle size test and call it a day.

issue.body:
I find this code snippet for change the global font-family. However, there is only one font.
```javascript
const customTheme = deepMerge(grommet, {
  paragraph: {
    global: {
      family: 'Comic Sans MS',
    },
  },
});
```
But we need to apply a lot of fonts to the font-family:
```css
body {
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "PingFang SC","Helvetica Neue",STHeiti,"Microsoft Yahei",Tahoma,Simsun,sans-serif;
}
```
How could we do?

